# Create word with automatic category classification
#
# Prerequisite: run docs/requests/auth/login.http first and copy the token.
#
# Behaviour:
#   - The "english_word" field is required.
#   - The API automatically calls Ollama (llama3.2) to classify the word
#     into 1-3 categories from the list: networking, databases, security, algorithms,
#     data-structures, operating-systems, programming-languages, web, cloud,
#     devops, hardware, artificial-intelligence, other.
#   - If Ollama is unavailable, the word is saved without categories (does not fail).
#   - The "categories" field is optional: if provided, skips automatic classification
#     and uses the given categories instead (manual override).
#
# Recommended extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client) for VS Code.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@token   = <paste-access_token-from-login-response-here>

###

# Automatic classification (no "categories" in the body — Ollama classifies)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/words
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "english_word": "firewall"
}

# Expected response (201 Created):
# {
#   "id": 1,
#   "word": "firewall",
#   "categories": [
#     { "slug": "networking", "name": "Networking" },
#     { "slug": "security",   "name": "Security" }
#   ],
#   "created_at": "2026-04-02T10:00:00.000000Z",
#   "updated_at": "2026-04-02T10:00:00.000000Z",
#   "translations": []
# }

###

# Manual category override (skips the Ollama call)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/words
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "english_word": "CPU",
  "categories": ["hardware"]
}
